# 1️⃣ Pointer vs Reference

---

# First Recall

Pointer:

```cpp
int x = 10;
int *p = &x;
```

Reference:

```cpp
int x = 10;
int &r = x;
```

Both seem similar.

But they are NOT the same.

---

# Mental Model

Think:

### Reference

```text
Nickname
```

Example:

```text
Virat Kohli
King Kohli
```

Same person.

Different names.

---

### Pointer

Think:

```text
Home Address
```

Example:

```text
House → Actual Data
Address → Pointer
```

Pointer stores address.

---

# Difference 1: Can It Be Null?

---

## Pointer

```cpp
int *p = nullptr;
```

✅ Valid

Means:

```text
Currently pointing nowhere
```

---

## Reference

```cpp
int &r;
```

❌ Invalid

Reference MUST refer to something.

---

# Why?

Because reference is just another name.

A nickname must belong to someone.

---

# Difference 2: Can It Change Target?

---

## Pointer

```cpp
int a = 10;
int b = 20;

int *p = &a;

p = &b;
```

✅ Allowed

Pointer can point somewhere else.

---

## Reference

```cpp
int a = 10;
int b = 20;

int &r = a;

r = b;
```

Many beginners think:

```text
Now r refers to b
```

❌ Wrong

Actually:

```cpp
a = b;
```

happens.

Reference remains tied to `a`.

---

# Mental Model

```text
Pointer = GPS Location
Can change destination

Reference = Permanent Nickname
Cannot switch person
```

---

# Difference 3: Memory

---

## Pointer

Stores address.

Needs its own memory.

```text
p → address
```

---

## Reference

Acts as alias.

No separate logical storage.

---

# Difference 4: Syntax

---

## Pointer

```cpp
*p
```

needed to access value.

---

## Reference

Use directly.

```cpp
r
```

---

# Interview Shortcut

| Feature            | Pointer | Reference |
| ------------------ | ------- | --------- |
| Stores address     | Yes     | No        |
| Can be null        | Yes     | No        |
| Can change target  | Yes     | No        |
| Dereference needed | Yes     | No        |

---

# Most Common Interview Answer

### When should you use Reference?

When:

```text
Object must always exist
```

and you don't want null checks.

---

### When should you use Pointer?

When:

```text
Object may be absent
```

or target must change.

---

# How to Remember Forever

```text
Reference = Alias

Pointer = Address Holder
```

