# 2️⃣ Memory Layout of a C++ Program

This topic is EXTREMELY important.

Interviewers love asking:

> Where does memory go?

---

# First Big Picture

A running C++ program is divided into parts:

```text
+------------------+
| Code Segment     |
+------------------+
| Data Segment     |
+------------------+
| Heap             |
+------------------+
| Stack            |
+------------------+
```

Think of memory as a building with floors.

Each floor has a job.

---

# A. Code Segment

---

Contains:

```text
Program Instructions
```

Example:

```cpp
cout << "Hello";
```

Machine instructions live here.

---

# Mental Model

```text
Recipe Book
```

Contains instructions only.

---

# B. Data Segment

Stores:

```text
Global Variables
Static Variables
```

---

## Example

```cpp
int globalVar = 100;
```

Stored here.

---

Why?

Because global variables must exist throughout program execution.

---

# Mental Model

```text
Permanent Storage Room
```

---

# C. Stack Memory

Most interview questions focus here.

---

## Example

```cpp
int main()
{
    int x = 10;
}
```

`x` lives in stack.

---

# Characteristics

✅ Fast

✅ Automatic

✅ Managed by compiler

---

# What Happens?

Function starts:

```text
Memory allocated
```

Function ends:

```text
Memory removed automatically
```

---

# Mental Model

```text
Temporary Work Desk
```

Use it.

Leave.

Clean automatically.

---

# Example

```cpp
void fun()
{
    int x = 10;
}
```

After function ends:

```text
x disappears
```

---

# D. Heap Memory

---

Created using:

```cpp
new
```

---

Example:

```cpp
int *p = new int;
```

Memory allocated in heap.

---

# Characteristics

✅ Flexible

✅ Dynamic

❌ Must manually free memory

---

# Example

```cpp
delete p;
```

---

# Mental Model

```text
Rental Warehouse
```

You rent space.

Must return it later.

---

# Stack vs Heap

Interviewers LOVE this.

| Stack            | Heap               |
| ---------------- | ------------------ |
| Automatic        | Manual             |
| Faster           | Slower             |
| Fixed Lifetime   | Flexible Lifetime  |
| Compiler Managed | Programmer Managed |

---

# Visual Example

```cpp
int main()
{
    int x = 10;

    int *p = new int;
}
```

Memory:

```text
STACK
-----
x
p

HEAP
----
allocated int
```

---

# Common Interview Question 🔥

### Why is Stack Faster?

Because:

```text
Automatic allocation/deallocation
```

Very simple.

---

### Why Use Heap?

Because:

```text
Need dynamic memory
```

Example:

```text
Unknown size at runtime
```

---

# Real-Life Analogy

### Stack

```text
Office Desk
```

Temporary work.

---

### Heap

```text
Storage Warehouse
```

Long-term storage.

---

